                     <title type="complete">I. Gadla Ḥawāryāt, Apocryphal Acts of the Apostles</title>
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <locus target="1ra">1ra</locus> (Introduction): በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ሥርዓቶሙ፡ ለሐዋርያት፡ ወባዕዳንሂ፡ እም፸ወ፪፡ አርድእት፡ ንኡሳን፡ ወዘኮነ፡ ኵሉ፡ እምዜናሆሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ብሔር፡ ወተዝካረ፡ ስምዕ፡ እምኔሆሙ፡ ወእለ፡ አዕረፉ፡ እምኔሆሙ፡ ጸሎቶሙ፡ ወበረከቶሙ፡ ትዕቀበነ፡ ለኵልነ፡ ሕዝብ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ለዓለም፡ አሜን፨… [<locus target="1vb">1vb</locus>]ንቀድም፡ በአኰቴተ፡ እግዚኣብሔር፡ በረድኤቱ፡ ለእግዚኣብሔር፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ስብከቱ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ኅሩይ፡ ሊቀ፡ ሐዋርያት፡…<foreign xml:lang="en">
                           <locus target="1ra">1ra</locus> (Introduction): In the Name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit. This (is) the book of the rule of the Apostles and of others among 72 lesser Disciples, and of all from their story that was in every country, and of the record (of those) of them who (suffered) the martyrdom and of those of them who died. May their prayer and their blessing take care of us, of all of us, Christian people. [Forever and] ever. Amen. ....  ]<locus target="1va">1va</locus>, l.17] With thanks of the Lord and with the help of the Lord Jesus Christ, we begin [to write] the preaching of the blessed [saint] Peter, the chosen chief of the Apostles…</foreign>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <locus target="182va">182va</locus>, l.30 (Dionysius on the tribes of the Apostles): …ወአኰቴት፡ ለመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዘ[<locus target="182vb">182vb</locus>]ወሀቦሙ፡ ጥበበ፡ ወአእምሮ፡ ከመ፡ ይስ[n.l.] ውስተ፡ ኵሉ፡ አጽ[n.l.] ዓለም፡ በእንተ፡ ቅድስት፡ ሥላሴ፡ ፩[n.l.]ላክ፡ ሎቱ፡ ስብሐት፡ ወክብር፡ ወዕበይ፡ እስከ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፨ ወአሜን፨ ለዘ፡ ጸሐፎ ወለዘ፡ አን[n.l.] ወለዘ፡ ተርጐሞ፡ ለዘሰምዐ፡ ቃላቲሁ፡ በአሚን፡ ወበርትዕ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ሕቡረ፡ [n.l.]ሐሮሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለዓለም፡ አሜን፨<foreign xml:lang="en">
                           <locus target="182va">182va</locus>, l.30 (Dionysius on the tribes of the Apostles): … And thanks-giving [be] to the Holy Spirit Who gave them knowledge and understanding so that [n.l.] in all [n.l.] the world concerning the Holy Trinity, one [God], to Whom [be] glory and honour and majesty, forever and ever. Amen. Amen. And for the one who wrote it and for whom [n.l.] and for the one who interpreted it, for the one who listened to its words in the belief and in the right faith, the Lord [be] in unison [n.l.], in the Reign of the Heavens. Forever. Amen.</foreign>
